-	Start program
-	Show menu – Available Items
-	Start loop
-	Prompt user to order items, view cart, or enter done.
-	Check if input items in menu  if in menu, validate input, ask for quantity
-	Else, if input not valid, ask user to enter valid inputs (i.e. Items displayed in menu only)
-	Loop until “Done” is entered
-	Calculate total of items in cart
-	Ask if user is a student  apply 5% discount
-	If, not student, no discount, continue to total
-	Calculate final total (subtotal – discount) + tax for student
-	OR subtotal + tax, if not student
-	Display receipt  List of items and quantities, subtotal, tax, discount (if applicable), final total
-	End
